column14: Q MMNT FROM MANNED BOAT APPROX 300M U/S OF GAUGE. FLOW WAS VERY SLOW MAKING HOLDING EDGE ESTIMATES DIFFICULT WITH THE CROSS WIND THAT WAS PRESENT. CROSS WIND BUT PRIMARILY BLOWING FROM U/S TO D/S @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ SL2 OFFSET UPON ARRIVAL = 3.864. NO RS IN SL2 AS REPLACING LOGGER TODAY.   NOTE TO RFT = STAGE IS CURRENTLY UNUSABLE AS PRESSURE LINE IS BLOCKED, DO NOT USE CALCULATED SRC FOUND AT 0850.  NOTE FOR RFT = PLEASE UPDATE HYDEX WITH REQUIRED INFORMATION TO CONTINUE INGESTION INTO AQ FOLLOWING THE ACTIONS TAKEN ON SITE NOTED BELOW:  INSTALLED NEW FTS ANTENNA (MODEL#1032-018 SERIAL# S15476981), REMOVED YAGI ANTENNA (MODEL # 18B, SERIAL #3380A01273)  REMOVED SL2 LOGGER AT 0905, (SL2 LOGGER MODEL # = SL2-G312-1, SERIAL # = 070746)  INSTALLED SL3 LOGGER (MODEL = SATLINK 3 LITE, SERIAL # = 24020539) INSTALLED 50M OTT ON ROCK ANCHOR (OTT PLS 500 SERIAL # = PS5-002058)  UPDATED GOES TO FROM 3 HR TX TO 1 HR TX WITH THE FOLLOWING: ID = 45431DE8 CH=40, FIRST TX = 00:34:05, RATE = 300 PERIOD = 01:00:00, TX WINDOW = 00:00:10  IN SL3 OLD OFFSET = 0, RS AT 1021, NEW OFFSET = 3.336 (NOTE AT 1028 REALIZED TIME OFFSET OF -420 MINUTES WAS APPLIED IN THE INCORRECT DIRECTION. THIS WAS CORRECTED FOR THE 1030 READING AND IN TIME FOR THE MMNT.  NOTE FOR RFT = LG2 LOGGER FILE ATTACHED TO RFT PACKAGE SHOWS RAW VALUES PRIOR TO THE CORRECTION OF THE DIRECTION OF THE TIME (420MIN) OFFSET. THERFORE LOGGER VALUE OF 00:20 = 10:20MST, 00:25 =10:25MST IN LG2.)  FINAL OFFSET UPON DEPARTURE = 3.336m, 1130 CUT INDICATED A RS WAS REQUIRED, HOWEVER THE CURRENT SURGE WAS = TO THE SRC SO ONSITE TECH DID NOT COMPLETE A RESET. ADCP by Moving Boat
